race.comment: FIORENOT (4) ran a strong race first up at Bendigo over 1300m when finding the line late to grab second. He was off a long break there so should strip much fitter and prove hard to hold out. TOUCHDOWN (13) is a lightly raced 4yo with a nice profile, winning at $1.16 fresh, good for second in a fast race at Ballarat. Drawn nicely, he should measure right up. JENNI MULTABELLA (11) is another with plenty of upside, beating the talented Polyglot on debut before resuming over a year later with a good second. She'll be fitter and takes beating. CHOKUTO (9) is a lightly raced gelding who won his maiden narrowly last time out at Sale. Further ground should suit even better, respecting.
